.TH "ef4_init_rx_buffers" 9 "ef4_init_rx_buffers" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ef4_init_rx_buffers \- create EF4_RX_BATCH page-based RX buffers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ef4_init_rx_buffers
.BI "(struct ef4_rx_queue *rx_queue "  ","
.BI "bool atomic "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rx_queue" 12
Efx RX queue
.IP "atomic" 12
control memory allocation flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This allocates a batch of pages, maps them for DMA, and populates
struct ef4_rx_buffers for each one. Return a negative error code or
0 on success. If a single page can be used for multiple buffers,
then the page will either be inserted fully, or not at all.
